"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-04-17-bbc-axe-olympic-legend-coverage-ahead-paris-games-20667442\", \"text\": \"TheBBChas sparked controversy after deciding not to use Olympic legend Sir Steve Redgrave as a pundit for their coverage of theParisGames.  The British hero won gold medals at five consecutive Games from 1984 to 2000 and is the most successful male rower in Olympic history.  Redgrave, 62, has featured regularly on the BBC's coverage since retirement but is now set to miss the upcomingOlympics, claiming he has lost his role as a pundit to Chair of UK Sport Dame Katherine Grainger.  The BBC allegedly decided it did not need three pundits and Redgrave has now been ditched, with Grainger and Sir Matthew Pinsent\\u00a0to cover the 2024 Games.  'I wasn't told that I have been discontinued, but it's sort of evolved,' Redgrave told theDaily Mail.  'Matt is the presenter and Katherine Grainger is the equivalent to what I was doing.  'The three of us worked together at the World Championships the year after Rio, but then they went, 'Male-female, covered on Olympic medals, why have three?'.  'Working for China [as a coach] at the last Games probably did not help matters.'  Redgrave walked off set in 2016 when the BBC did not show the whole of the Helen Glover-Heather Stanning women's pair semi-final live at the Rio Games.  'There is absolutely no issue between the BBC and Sir Steve Redgrave,' the BBC said in a statement at the time.  Redgrave is still open to working as a pundit for the Games in Paris if he is approached by another broadcaster.  Quizzed how he would respond to a last-minute SOS, Redgrave said: 'If someone said, 'Would you help us through to LA [2028]?', that would be a harder decision to make. But to, 'Will you help us out for Paris?', the answer would be yes, I am sure.'  There has been plenty of reaction to Redgrave's omission on social media with one user, @perks_joanna, posting on X: 'I hope he gets a last minute Hail Mary pass. It would not be a proper rowing event without the mighty Sir Steve.'  ArrowMORE:BBC star reveals 'terrible' payslip from iconic TV show  ArrowMORE:BBC fans fear the worst for 'best ever crime drama'  ArrowMORE:Strictly star 'confirmed for 2024 BBC series line-up' ahead of professionals tour  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"